[1] New York state
Date: Thu 1 Apr 2010
Source: WCAX, Local Vermont News [edited]
<http://www.wcax.com/Global/story.asp?S=12239717>


9 confirmed mumps cases at Plattsburgh State
--------------------------------------------
Health officials say there are now more confirmed cases of mumps
virus infection at Plattsburgh State [college]. School officials say
there are now 9 confirmed cases with 6 more pending. Affected
students are reportedly only showing mild symptoms like fever, aches
and swollen glands.

The school is insisting that everyone be vaccinated. Students can get
the vaccine for free at the health center on campus or at any county
health department.

--
